09:24.696 --> 09:25.796
  Edith, Edith, where are you?  

09:25.798 --> 09:27.632
EDITH: In the                   
kitchen, Archie.                

09:27.634 --> 09:29.467
Oh, you're in the kitchen, huh? 

09:29.469 --> 09:31.469
Why didn't you wake me up       
     a little bit earlier?      

09:31.471 --> 09:33.471
            It's after 5 a.m.,  
          I'm gonna have to rush

09:33.473 --> 09:34.472
                    to make that
                fishing boat.   

09:34.474 --> 09:36.440
You've got                      
plenty of time.                 

09:36.442 --> 09:38.809
          Edith, and the house  
        is as cold as an icebox.

09:38.811 --> 09:40.411
              Didn't you think  
            to turn up the heat?

09:40.413 --> 09:41.812
    Oh, I don't think           
    we should, Archie,          

09:41.814 --> 09:44.081
not with the energy crisis.     

09:44.083 --> 09:45.616
     Oh, the energy crisis.     

09:45.618 --> 09:48.553
 I wish you would come up with  
one of them hot flashes of yours

09:48.555 --> 09:50.188
      now that we need it.      

09:51.923 --> 09:53.957
    Come on, come on.           

09:53.959 --> 09:56.794
Here's your coffee.             
Now, I got everything ready.    

09:56.796 --> 09:58.462
                    Oh, yeah?   
Oh, yeah.                       

09:58.464 --> 10:00.764
I've been up                    
a couple of hours.              

10:00.766 --> 10:03.133
             I couldn't sleep   
            last night.         

10:03.135 --> 10:07.171
         I think because of     
      what Gloria said to us.   

10:07.173 --> 10:08.506
          Oh, listen,           
     that daughter of yours     

10:08.508 --> 10:09.773
is pretty fresh there, you know.

10:09.775 --> 10:11.409
      People tell me that       
    she's got my eyes,          

10:11.411 --> 10:15.413
    but that mouth of hers,     
that's your side of the family. 

10:15.415 --> 10:18.115
 Imagine a daughter saying them 
things to her mother and father.

10:18.117 --> 10:21.285
         I don't think          
    that was Gloria talking.    

10:21.287 --> 10:24.555
         Oh, gee, what,         
the devil make her do it?       

10:24.557 --> 10:28.259
Maybe I ought to get one of them
priests in to exercise with her.

10:34.766 --> 10:39.303
         No, something          
     was bothering Gloria,      

10:39.305 --> 10:43.006
so she took it out on the people
    that are closest to her.    

10:43.008 --> 10:44.442
Well, what kind of talk is that,

10:44.444 --> 10:46.477
        she don't wanna         
      end up like us, huh?      

10:46.479 --> 10:48.078
We didn't end up so bad, did we?

10:48.080 --> 10:50.080
     I always did all right     
    by you, didn't I?           

10:50.082 --> 10:51.181
        Oh, yeah.               

10:51.183 --> 10:52.583
After all, you got a nice life. 

10:52.585 --> 10:54.252
      You got a home here.      

10:54.254 --> 10:56.621
        You got clothes,        
 you got a color TV out there.  

10:56.623 --> 10:59.990
You got all the dishes you need.

10:59.992 --> 11:02.293
    Can you ask for anything    
      I wouldn't give you?      

11:02.295 --> 11:06.897
Well, I could use another       
$10 a week for the house money. 

11:06.899 --> 11:10.234
 Well, you ain't getting that.  

11:10.236 --> 11:12.870
Yeah. Well, here you are.       

11:12.872 --> 11:15.273
            Where are you going?
          I better call Mike.   

11:15.275 --> 11:16.741
You mean to tell me             
that meathead                   

11:16.743 --> 11:18.075
ain't been down                 
to breakfast yet?               

11:18.077 --> 11:20.077
                    No.         
Get out of the way.             
I'll call him myself.           

11:20.079 --> 11:23.080
You can't depend                
on that guy for nothing.        

11:25.016 --> 11:27.184
Well, what are you doing up     
so early, little girl?          

11:27.186 --> 11:28.686
            I couldn't sleep.   

11:28.688 --> 11:29.953
Oh, well,                       
I'm not surprised.              

11:29.955 --> 11:32.222
How could anybody sleep         
in a crummy house like this?    

11:32.224 --> 11:35.225
      Oh, Daddy, I'm sorry      
 about what I said last night.  

11:35.227 --> 11:36.827
You're sorry? Well,             
that goes double for me.        

11:36.829 --> 11:38.696
             Daddy, please don't
              be angry with me. 

11:38.698 --> 11:40.298
                 I didn't know  
              what I was saying.

11:40.300 --> 11:42.700
     I mean, whatever I said,   
  it had nothing to do with you.

11:42.702 --> 11:44.101
                 I guess I was  
              talking that way--

11:44.103 --> 11:45.703
Hold it. Hold it.               
Hold it. Hold it.               

11:45.705 --> 11:49.106
If it's female,                 
don't tell me, huh?             

11:49.108 --> 11:50.908
I just want to know             
how you are.                    

11:50.910 --> 11:51.909
Are you all right?              

11:51.911 --> 11:54.378
                Yeah, Daddy.    
                  I'm all right.

11:54.380 --> 11:56.380
Well, if you're gonna           
sit down here, it's cold.       

11:56.382 --> 11:57.981
Maybe you ought to get          
your blanket, huh?              

11:57.983 --> 11:59.183
                  No, thank you.

11:59.185 --> 12:01.018
Why don't you                   
go back up to bed?              

12:01.020 --> 12:03.887
              Oh, no. I'm afraid
              I'll wake Michael.

12:03.889 --> 12:05.289
      You'll wake Michael?      

12:05.291 --> 12:07.991
  You mean to tell me he ain't  
     out of that sack yet?      

12:07.993 --> 12:10.761
The one time I wanted him       
with me, and he ain't here!     

12:10.763 --> 12:13.130
      That bum could sleep      
        a hundred years.        

12:16.768 --> 12:19.537
                     Oh, jeez,  
                look at this.   

12:19.539 --> 12:22.172
            Rip Van Meathead.   

12:23.608 --> 12:25.409
            Get up out of there.
I'm up. I'm up.                 

12:25.411 --> 12:27.411
      Get out of the bed, there!
          What are you doing?   

12:27.413 --> 12:28.479
              Here's your pants.
Sh, sh!                         

12:28.481 --> 12:29.780
        Get them on you, huh?   
Sh!                             

12:29.782 --> 12:31.415
                 I can never    
             depend on you for--

12:31.417 --> 12:33.617
            Hold it! Hold it!   
        What are you doing here?

12:33.619 --> 12:36.019
    You're putting your pants on
         over your pajamas.     

12:36.021 --> 12:38.021
It's all right.                 
It'll be cold on the boat.      

12:38.023 --> 12:39.590
I don't have                    
any long underwear.             

12:39.592 --> 12:40.991
                  All right,    
             just hurry up, huh?

12:40.993 --> 12:42.025
Will you shush!                 

12:42.027 --> 12:43.026
                     Why are you
                    shushing me?

12:43.028 --> 12:44.995
I don't want to                 
wake up Gloria!                 

12:44.997 --> 12:47.998
              Gloria ain't here!
            She's downstairs.   

12:50.969 --> 12:52.135
What's she doing                
     downstairs?                

12:52.137 --> 12:53.604
She's sitting                   
in a chair down there.          

12:53.606 --> 12:54.605
She's all right.                

12:54.607 --> 12:56.273
                How do you know?
She told me.                    

12:56.275 --> 12:57.274
                What did        
                she say?        

12:57.276 --> 12:59.677
She said, "I'm all right."      

12:59.679 --> 13:01.645
Will you                        
hurry it up, please!            

13:01.647 --> 13:03.080
    Oh, I was worried           
        about her.              

13:03.082 --> 13:04.715
        Last night              
    she wouldn't talk to me.    

13:04.717 --> 13:06.917
It was like there was           
a pane of glass between us.     

13:06.919 --> 13:08.919
    Do you know that we don't   
        catch that fishing boat,

13:08.921 --> 13:10.488
            there ain't gonna be
            no deep-sea fishing.

13:10.490 --> 13:12.690
  We'll have to stay on the dock
    with the old people.        

13:12.692 --> 13:13.891
            Hold it. Hold it.   
                    Hold it!    

13:13.893 --> 13:15.092
                    What are you
                     doing here?

13:15.094 --> 13:16.427
         What?                  

13:16.429 --> 13:19.697
                    What about  
                 the other foot?

13:19.699 --> 13:21.866
                    There ain't 
                  no sock on it.

13:21.868 --> 13:24.301
I'll get to it.                 

13:24.303 --> 13:28.138
 Don't you know that the whole  
world puts on a sock and a sock 

13:28.140 --> 13:30.441
     and a shoe and a shoe?     

13:36.782 --> 13:39.683
     I like to take care of     
      one foot at a time.       

13:41.453 --> 13:44.955
    That's the dumbest thing    
  I've ever heard in my life!   

13:44.957 --> 13:47.357
It's just as quick              
my way.                         

13:47.359 --> 13:49.192
            Wait a minute.      
        That ain't the point.   

13:49.194 --> 13:51.194
              You see, what I-- 
            Don't keep doing it!

13:51.196 --> 13:53.063
                Listen to me!   

13:54.999 --> 13:56.400
          Suppose there's a fire
            in the house        

13:56.402 --> 13:58.869
        and you've got to run   
            for your life.      

13:58.871 --> 14:02.773
     Your way, all you've got on
    is one shoe and a sock.     

14:02.775 --> 14:05.509
        My way, you've got on   
             a sock and a sock. 

14:05.511 --> 14:06.644
        You see? You're even.   

14:12.417 --> 14:14.718
Suppose it's raining            
or snowing outside.             

14:14.720 --> 14:17.154
Your way, with a sock           
on each foot,                   

14:17.156 --> 14:18.422
my feet would get wet.          

14:18.424 --> 14:21.158
My way, with a sock             
and a shoe on one foot,         

14:21.160 --> 14:24.328
I could hop around              
and stay dry.                   

14:31.670 --> 14:35.539
         I think you've been    
    hopping around on your head.

14:35.541 --> 14:38.709
              Wait a minute.    
          Wait a-- Listen to me!

14:41.746 --> 14:43.581
      Supposing the other sock's
        got a hole in it.       

14:43.583 --> 14:44.982
It doesn't have                 
a hole in it.                   

14:44.984 --> 14:46.917
             I said supposing   
          it's got a hole in it.

14:46.919 --> 14:48.418
All right, suppose              
it has a hole.                  

14:48.420 --> 14:50.020
             All right, it's got
                a hole in it.   

14:50.022 --> 14:51.455
             So you ain't got   
          another matching pair,

14:51.457 --> 14:52.857
                 so what are you
                    gonna do?   

14:52.859 --> 14:56.193
    Your way, you gotta take off
      a whole shoe and a sock.  

14:56.195 --> 15:00.030
        My way, all you gotta do
          is take off one sock. 

15:00.032 --> 15:01.431
All right, if it'll             
make you happy,                 

15:01.433 --> 15:02.700
I'll start                      
all over again.                 

15:02.702 --> 15:05.936
             No! Not now!       
     You're halfway through now!

15:05.938 --> 15:08.772
        Jeez, get on with it.   
             We're in a hurry.  

15:10.208 --> 15:13.443
     You can start doing it     
the right way tomorrow morning. 

15:13.445 --> 15:15.613
    And do it that way          
for the rest of your life!      

15:24.422 --> 15:27.791
Gloria. Oh, I brought you       
some juice.                     

15:27.793 --> 15:29.793
Drink all of it.                

15:29.795 --> 15:35.566
You never can tell what part    
the vitamin C might be in.      

15:35.568 --> 15:37.968
Boy, I want to tell you there's 
some people in this world       

15:37.970 --> 15:39.570
you can never get nothing       
through their heads.            

15:39.572 --> 15:40.638
         Look who's up.         

15:40.640 --> 15:41.939
I know who's up.                

15:41.941 --> 15:44.141
Do you know who's got to        
get out of here, huh?           

15:44.143 --> 15:45.442
Will you get                    
my lunch ready?                 

15:45.444 --> 15:46.911
    Oh, yeah,                   
right away, Arch.               

15:46.913 --> 15:51.114
Listen, little girl, you mind if
 I ask you a personal question? 

15:51.116 --> 15:52.616
GLORIA:                         
No.                             

15:52.618 --> 15:55.886
Did you ever watch your husband 
 dress himself in the morning?  

15:55.888 --> 15:57.988
                Sometimes.      

15:57.990 --> 15:59.456
Did you know                    
that he puts on                 

15:59.458 --> 16:01.659
a sock and a shoe               
and a sock and a shoe           

16:01.661 --> 16:04.562
instead of a sock and a sock    
and a shoe and a shoe?          

16:06.031 --> 16:08.498
                  What?         

16:08.500 --> 16:13.203
What's the sense in asking you? 
      You wear pantyhose.       

16:13.205 --> 16:15.539
                Gloria.         
Oh, here he is.                 

16:15.541 --> 16:17.975
Now, will you get your gear     
together and get ready to leave?

16:17.977 --> 16:19.443
      We gotta get going!       

16:19.445 --> 16:21.845
    Take it easy, will you?     
I want to talk to Gloria first. 

16:21.847 --> 16:23.080
We've got a boat                
to catch.                       

16:23.082 --> 16:24.247
                Don't worry.    
                  We'll make it.

16:24.249 --> 16:26.083
Here's your lunch,              
Archie.                         

16:26.085 --> 16:27.284
                 Leave it there,
                      Edith.    

16:27.286 --> 16:28.518
                     Gloria,    
                how do you feel?

16:28.520 --> 16:29.920
     Fine.                      

16:29.922 --> 16:31.755
                You want me     
          to stay home with you?

16:31.757 --> 16:33.057
Whatever you like.              

16:33.059 --> 16:34.858
    Because, you know,          
  I don't have to go fishing.   

16:34.860 --> 16:36.026
    Do what you want.           

16:36.028 --> 16:37.728
    Well, what do you want?     
         Just tell me.          

16:37.730 --> 16:40.530
    Go fishing.                 
                You're sure?    

16:40.532 --> 16:44.267
Michael, if you want to         
go fishing, go fishing.         

16:44.269 --> 16:45.703
            Gloria,             
      where are you going?      

16:45.705 --> 16:46.770
                    Back to bed.

16:46.772 --> 16:49.406
Oh, don't go away.              
I want to talk to you.          

16:49.408 --> 16:50.407
                     What about?

16:50.409 --> 16:52.843
 Uh, well, just wait            
      a minute.                 

16:52.845 --> 16:55.312
Okay. Okay. We're all set.      
Let's go now, huh?              

16:55.314 --> 16:57.114
Wait a second. Wait a second.   
I forgot something.             

16:57.116 --> 16:58.348
                    What are you
                     doing now? 

16:58.350 --> 16:59.650
                    Bye, honey. 

16:59.652 --> 17:01.885
        Oh, look at this.       
      He's got to stop for that.

17:01.887 --> 17:03.954
    Okay, you gotta wait        
 for me now. I forgot something.

17:03.956 --> 17:06.924
Oh, Archie!                     

17:10.694 --> 17:12.963
Get out of the way, Edith.      

17:15.398 --> 17:17.835
                    What did    
                     you forget?

17:17.837 --> 17:20.671
        My six-pack             
          of beer.              

17:20.673 --> 17:22.271
            You can't go fishing
             without beer, Edie.

17:22.273 --> 17:23.741
                 Okay, let's go.

17:23.742 --> 17:26.644
Now, watch the poles! Don't     
hit them on the top of the door.

17:26.646 --> 17:29.713
        Here, hold them this way
    on the vertizontal there.   

17:29.715 --> 17:32.082
        Okay, that's right.     
         Now, come on. Let's go.

17:32.084 --> 17:33.117
        [FISHING POLES CRACK]   

17:33.119 --> 17:35.519
                  [ARCHIE YELLS]

17:38.523 --> 17:42.660
        ARCHIE: You're a killer.
          That's what you are!  

17:42.662 --> 17:46.496
    Have a good time.           

17:46.498 --> 17:49.033
          Oh, Gloria,           

17:49.035 --> 17:51.601
you still ain't feeling good,   
              are you?          

17:51.603 --> 17:53.303
    I feel awful.               

17:53.305 --> 17:55.005
            Well, come on out   
                in the kitchen. 

17:55.007 --> 17:56.807
                I'll fix you    
                 some breakfast.

17:56.809 --> 17:59.910
        You can keep me company,
             and we'll talk.    

17:59.912 --> 18:02.179
                  Here, you sit 
                 right down here

18:02.181 --> 18:05.215
    and I'll have some nice     
     scrambled eggs for you     

18:05.217 --> 18:07.350
          in a jiffy.           

18:08.486 --> 18:11.555
Speaking of eggs, Gloria,       

18:11.557 --> 18:14.858
      before Archie and me      
          got married,          

18:14.860 --> 18:16.727
        he used to              
    go around saying,           

18:16.729 --> 18:20.297
      "There's no cooking       
    like my mother's."          

18:20.299 --> 18:23.934
         So I went over         
        to his mother's,        

18:23.936 --> 18:28.572
    and she showed me           
    how to cook for Archie.     

18:28.574 --> 18:35.212
 Oh, my, I'll never forget the  
 first time I served him eggs.  

18:35.214 --> 18:39.950
        He took a bite,         
 and a look came over his face. 

18:39.952 --> 18:41.785
 I said, "Don't you like them?" 

18:41.787 --> 18:44.254
 He said, "Edith, I always said 

18:44.256 --> 18:46.356
     "there's nothing like      
      my mother's cooking       

18:46.358 --> 18:49.059
     and here it is again!"     

18:49.061 --> 18:50.393
          That's nice.          

18:50.395 --> 18:53.997
          No, he hated          
     his mother's cooking.      

18:55.767 --> 19:00.170
 I had to start all over again. 

19:00.172 --> 19:04.141
     Now your father likes      
     your mother's cooking.     

19:04.143 --> 19:06.576
        [GIGGLING]              

19:06.578 --> 19:07.644
            Get it?             

19:07.646 --> 19:11.148
     Ma, how do you do it?      

19:11.150 --> 19:13.683
  How do you stay so cheerful   
         all the time?          

19:13.685 --> 19:18.222
  Oh, I'm sad a lot of times.   

19:18.224 --> 19:22.059
Regular times, when people die, 

19:22.061 --> 19:26.029
    and once, once, Gloria--    

19:26.031 --> 19:29.199
    I haven't thought           
      about it for years.       

19:29.201 --> 19:30.868
It was terrible.                

19:30.870 --> 19:36.006
It was the day I was sure I     
didn't love your father no more.

19:36.008 --> 19:38.976
                     Really, Ma?

19:38.978 --> 19:40.944
                    You stopped 
                loving Daddy?   

19:40.946 --> 19:43.546
                  What did he do
                      to you?   

19:43.548 --> 19:45.315
That's just the point.          

19:45.317 --> 19:46.616
      Nothing.                  

19:46.618 --> 19:50.020
He'd come home one night        
and said hello                  

19:50.022 --> 19:51.421
and I said hello.               

19:51.423 --> 19:54.557
And he sat down in his chair    
to read his paper               

19:54.559 --> 19:58.829
just like he'd done             
a thousand times before.        

19:58.831 --> 20:03.000
You know how he licks his       
fingers when he turns the page: 

20:06.137 --> 20:09.072
I looked at him.                

20:15.046 --> 20:18.448
All of a sudden                 
he was a stranger.              

20:18.450 --> 20:20.050
I didn't know him,              

20:20.052 --> 20:23.153
and what's worse,               
I didn't want to know him.      

20:24.588 --> 20:28.525
      Ma, the same thing's      
        happened to me.         

20:28.527 --> 20:30.894
              No!               

20:30.896 --> 20:32.729
        You knew!               

20:32.731 --> 20:34.932
              No!               

20:34.934 --> 20:39.336
    Oh, well, it wasn't hard    
         to figure out.         

20:39.338 --> 20:41.771
When you told Mike to go fishing

20:41.773 --> 20:45.742
your face looked the way I felt 
     that day with Archie.      

20:45.744 --> 20:49.913
Now I understand why you talked 
to your father and me that way. 

20:49.915 --> 20:52.015
          Because when          
you're feeling like that,       

20:52.017 --> 20:55.018
     you don't like nothing     
        about your life.        

20:55.020 --> 20:59.089
    Yeah. Ma, you know when     
  it happened? Two nights ago?  

20:59.091 --> 21:01.892
You know, I was upstairs,       
 it was the middle of the night 

21:01.894 --> 21:03.927
         and I woke up,         
 and I looked over at Michael.  

21:03.929 --> 21:06.029
  Well, there he was, asleep,   

21:06.031 --> 21:09.299
    grinding his teeth          
      like he always does.      

21:09.301 --> 21:11.301
         But just like          
    it happened to you, Ma,     

21:11.303 --> 21:13.737
        all of a sudden,        
    I didn't recognize him.     

21:13.739 --> 21:16.606
    It was like I was           
sleeping with a stranger.       

21:16.608 --> 21:20.477
      And you were scared       
  you didn't love him no more.  

21:20.479 --> 21:22.645
         That's right.          

21:22.647 --> 21:25.515
        And Ma, what if         
      I don't get over it?      

21:25.517 --> 21:30.988
Gloria, all I can tell you      
 is I got over it the next day. 

21:30.990 --> 21:35.025
Archie came home, he said,      
    "Hello. Get me a beer,"     

21:35.027 --> 21:38.495
    and I was in love.          

21:38.497 --> 21:39.963
        Just like that?         

21:39.965 --> 21:41.198
Yeah!                           

21:41.200 --> 21:43.066
      That's how you knew       
     you loved Daddy again,     

21:43.068 --> 21:45.269
    "Hello. Get me a beer"?     

21:45.271 --> 21:46.904
  That's the way it happened.   

21:46.906 --> 21:49.839
You know, I think a lot of      
    marriages break up          

21:49.841 --> 21:52.509
because people don't wait       
          long enough           

21:52.511 --> 21:55.112
 to recognize each other again. 

21:57.282 --> 21:58.282
                  Gloria?       

21:58.284 --> 21:59.482
It's Mike!                      

21:59.484 --> 22:01.484
                 What's he doing
                    back home?  

22:01.486 --> 22:02.752
Mike! What are you              
doing home?                     

22:02.754 --> 22:04.922
Did you                         
forget something?               

22:04.924 --> 22:06.523
                No, I got as far
                 as the subway. 

22:06.525 --> 22:07.757
                I was so worried
                  about Gloria  

22:07.759 --> 22:09.426
              that I told Archie
            to go without me.   

22:09.428 --> 22:11.728
You were worried                
about me?                       

22:11.730 --> 22:13.163
          Yeah, I knew something
            was bothering you.  

22:13.165 --> 22:14.197
                  I've just been
                avoiding it.    

22:14.199 --> 22:15.532
                  I shouldn't   
              have gone fishing.

22:15.534 --> 22:16.533
                 When you've got
                    a problem,  

22:16.535 --> 22:17.734
             I've got a problem.

22:17.736 --> 22:19.536
    I should have stayed home   
        and dealt with it.      

22:19.538 --> 22:21.138
      And can we talk about this
            over breakfast?     

22:21.140 --> 22:22.806
                     I'm hungry.

22:22.808 --> 22:23.840
      Ma,                       

22:23.842 --> 22:25.675
          did you hear          
         what he said?          

22:25.677 --> 22:27.411
            He said,            
         "I'm hungry"!          

22:27.413 --> 22:28.412
    [LAUGHS EXCITEDLY]          

22:28.414 --> 22:31.181
      Michael, I love you!      

22:40.891 --> 22:43.293
              [LAUGHING HAPPILY]

22:43.295 --> 22:48.165
                 Oh, Ma, Ma,    
             isn't he beautiful?

22:54.305 --> 22:56.539
        What's so funny?        

22:56.541 --> 22:57.807
    Oh, nothing.                

22:57.809 --> 23:01.445
We was just talking about       
a couple of strangers we know.  

23:01.447 --> 23:02.446
        [BOTH LAUGHING]         

23:03.948 --> 23:05.849
    Everything's all right?     

23:05.851 --> 23:06.850
It's perfect.                   

23:06.852 --> 23:09.052
                Oh, I'm glad,   
                    honey.      

23:09.054 --> 23:11.955
          Yeah. Now there's only
            one little problem. 

23:11.957 --> 23:13.790
GLORIA:                         
What?                           

23:13.792 --> 23:16.293
 I've got Archie's fishing rod. 

23:26.704 --> 23:29.239
                  Edith.        

23:29.241 --> 23:31.274
Archie! You're back.            

23:31.276 --> 23:35.545
                Where is that   
                  dumb meathead?

23:35.547 --> 23:38.982
He and Gloria went out          
for a pizza.                    

23:38.984 --> 23:43.753
        I hope an anchovy       
    gets stuck in his throat.   

23:43.755 --> 23:46.056
    Do you know what happened   
            because of him?     

23:46.058 --> 23:50.360
     I had to lay out 5 bucks   
 to rent a no-good fishing pole.

23:50.362 --> 23:52.629
Did you catch something?        

23:52.631 --> 23:54.164
                Oh, sure, Edith.

23:54.166 --> 23:58.101
I caught a whale, but I couldn't
  bring him home on the subway. 

23:58.103 --> 24:00.037
[GIGGLING]                      

24:00.039 --> 24:01.838
                [MOCKS GIGGLING]

24:01.840 --> 24:04.641
                 Will you get me
                     a beer?    

24:04.643 --> 24:06.510
Right away.                     

24:23.561 --> 24:26.863
             [♪]                

